## Instructions

Implement the task defined in the change directory.
Work in focused chunks of 3-5 cohesive files at a time.
- It's fine to tackle the next comingled tasks in the same session if needed, but don't do too much;
  - **NEVER work on more than one task section at a time.**
  - Stop when you feel you've done enough cohesive work and it's good to pause. (like you were working on a pomodoro 20min session)

### Implementation Process

1. Read the task specification from the change path
2. Identify the next chunk of work (related files/functionality)
3. Implement the chunk following project conventions

**OpenSpec requirement**: if you have the skill `opsx:apply` available, use it with the change path folder name as argument.

**TDD requirement**: If the task introduces new code (functions, classes, modules), use the skill `test-driven-development`.

**Skip test-driven-development when**:
- Infrastructure/config tasks (CI, build, linting setup)
- The task IS writing tests or e2e tests 
  - Never use Mocks on E2E tests, the idea is to stress the real system with real APIs. Unless the user explicitly asked to use mocks.
- Writing frontend or UI/UX code. 
  - Here you should favor happy paths and basic unhappy flows using e2e/playwright tests
  - Apply TDD in E2E imagining you are the user
  - Use the `webapp-testing` skill to run your tests
  - Use the `frontend-design` skill for design tasks.
- Pure refactoring with existing test coverage

4. Verify the chunk works before proceeding

### Self-Check Before Signaling

Before signaling completion of a chunk, verify:

- [ ] Code compiles/type-checks without errors
- [ ] New functionality is wired up and callable
- [ ] If it's a UI/frontend task use the `webapp-testing` skill to verify it works
- [ ] No TODO comments left unaddressed
- [ ] Tests pass for the changed code
- [ ] Code follows project style guidelines

- [ ] Run `/remove-ai-slop` to clean up:
    - Unnecessary comments
    - Over-defensive code
    - Type casts to `any`
    - Style inconsistencies
    - Remove dead code introduced and review code that should be wired and it's not

### Signals

When you complete a cohesive chunk but more work remains:
```
<aop>CHUNK_DONE</aop>
```

When all implementation tasks are complete:
```
<aop>ALL_TASKS_DONE</aop>
```

Do not signal until the self-check passes. If blocked, describe the issue clearly.
